MENINGITIS - DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF CONGO (EX-ZAIRE)
****************************************************
See Also
Meningitis, meningococcal - West Africa 970323133337
Meningitis, meningococcal - West Africa (02) 970328212131
Meningitis, meningococcal - West Africa (03) 970412205719
Meningitis, meningococcal - West Africa (04) 970502140404
Meningitis, meningococcal - West Africa: Correction 970422104300
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 1997 22:52:18 -0400 (EDT)
Via: IntrTrack1@aol.com
Source: newsmedia, 17 Jul 1997

Meningitis has killed at least 16 people in two towns of the Democratic
Republic of the Congo, Dr Florimont Tshiogo of the World Health
Organization said in Kinshasa July 17. [Type unspecified, presumably
meningococcal; WHO has not yet got it up on their Outbreaks Page as of this
hour - Mod.JW

In Kamina, in the southern province of Shaba, the outbreak began in March
1997, and there have been 25 cases including 7 deaths.
The epidemic in Kindu, in the central Maniema province, began 9 days ago,
with 21 cases reported, including 9 deaths.
WHO said both epidemics had been brought under control.
............................................................jw
